## 3. Data Architecture (Metaobjects & Metafields)

This step creates the custom data types that power the theme's dynamic features. **If you ran the setup script, these are already created** — verify they exist.

### 3.1 Metaobject Definitions

Create these in **Settings > Custom data > Metaobjects**.

> **CRITICAL:** Enable **Storefront access** on ALL metaobject definitions. Without this, the theme cannot read metaobject data on the storefront.

#### 3.1.1 Benefit (`benefit`)

**Create this FIRST** — the Ingredient definition references it.

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Definition name | `Benefit` |
| Type handle | `benefit` |
| Storefront access | **Enabled** |
| Web pages | Not required |

| Field Handle | Display Name | Type | Required |
|---|---|---|---|
| `title` | Title | Single-line text | Yes |
| `description` | Description | Single-line text | No |
| `category` | Category | Single-line text | No |
| `icon_label` | Icon Label | Single-line text | No |

#### 3.1.2 FAQ Entry (`faq_entry`)

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Definition name | `FAQ Entry` |
| Type handle | `faq_entry` |
| Storefront access | **Enabled** |
| Web pages | Not required |

| Field Handle | Display Name | Type | Required |
|---|---|---|---|
| `question` | Question | Single-line text | Yes |
| `answer` | Answer | Rich text | Yes |

> **Usage:** FAQ entries are referenced per-product via `product.metafields.custom.faqs` and rendered in an accordion on the product page.

#### 3.1.3 Blog Author (`blog_author`)

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Definition name | `Blog Author` |
| Type handle | `blog_author` |
| Storefront access | **Enabled** |
| Web pages | Not required |

| Field Handle | Display Name | Type | Required |
|---|---|---|---|
| `name` | Name | Single-line text | Yes |
| `bio` | Bio | Single-line text | No |
| `avatar` | Avatar | File reference (image) | No |

> Avatar should be a square image, minimum 96x96px.

#### 3.1.4 Ingredient (`ingredient`)

**Create this LAST** — it references the `benefit` definition.

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Definition name | `Ingredient` |
| Type handle | `ingredient` |
| Storefront access | **Enabled** |
| Web pages | **Enabled** (creates browsable `/pages/ingredient-name` URLs) |

| Field Handle | Display Name | Type | Required | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `name` | Name | Single-line text | Yes | Display name |
| `inci_name` | INCI Name | Single-line text | No | Scientific INCI nomenclature |
| `benefits` | Benefits | List of metaobject references → `benefit` | No | Links to benefit entries |
| `one_line_benefit` | One-Line Benefit | Single-line text | No | Short benefit tagline for cards |
| `description` | Description | Rich text | No | Full ingredient description |
| `source` | Source | Single-line text | No | Where the ingredient is sourced from |
| `origin` | Origin | Single-line text | No | Country/region of origin |
| `category` | Category | Single-line text | No | Type (e.g., "Botanical", "Peptide", "Vitamin") — used for filtering |
| `concern` | Concern | Single-line text | No | Hair concern (e.g., "Hair Loss", "Hydration", "Scalp Health") — used for filtering |
| `image` | Image | File reference (image) | No | Main ingredient image |
| `icon` | Icon | File reference (image) | No | Small icon for grid cards |
| `science_images` | Science Images | List of file references | No | Gallery of science/research images |
| `is_hero` | Is Hero | Boolean | No | Flags featured/star ingredients |
| `sort_order` | Sort Order | Integer | No | Manual ordering (lower = first) |
| `collection` | Collection | Collection reference | No | Associated product collection |

