## 4. Pages

Create the following pages in **Online Store > Pages**. The **handle must match exactly** — the theme links to these handles internally.

| Page Title | Handle (URL slug) | Template Suffix | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Ingredients** | `ingredients` | `ingredients` | Ingredient library hub. Leave body empty — content is rendered by the template. |
| **Quiz** | `quiz` | `quiz` | Hair diagnosis quiz. Body content is not displayed. |
| **Quiz Results** | `quiz-results` | `quiz-results` | AI-powered quiz results. Results are loaded dynamically. |
| **Contact** | `contact` | `contact` | Contact form. Standard Shopify contact form. |

> **Note:** Two additional pages (Store Locator and Pharmacy Partners) are covered in the Optional Add-Ons section at the end of this guide.

### How to set the template suffix

After creating each page:
1. In the Shopify admin, go to **Online Store > Pages**
2. Click the page name
3. In the right sidebar under **Theme template**, select the matching template from the dropdown
4. Save

