## 5. Blog Setup

### 5.1 Create the Blog

1. Go to **Online Store > Blog posts**
2. Click **Manage blogs** (top right)
3. Create a new blog — name it "Journal", "Blog", or whatever fits your brand
4. Note the blog handle (URL slug) — you'll need it for navigation

### 5.2 Template Assignment

1. Go to **Online Store > Themes > Customize**
2. In the top dropdown, select **Blogs > Default blog** (or your blog name)
3. Assign the `blog.tara` template
4. Then select **Blog posts > Default blog post**
5. Assign the `article.tara` template

### 5.3 Create Blog Author Entries

1. Go to **Content > Metaobjects > Blog Author** (or **Settings > Custom data > Metaobjects > blog_author**)
2. Click **Add entry**
3. Fill in: Name, Bio (e.g., "Founder & Herbalist"), Avatar (square, 96x96px minimum)
4. Create an entry for each author who will write blog posts

### 5.4 Article Content Best Practices

- Use `<h2>` and `<h3>` headings in article body — the **Table of Contents is auto-generated** from these
- Set `custom.featured = true` on **one article** per blog for the hero spotlight
- Populate `custom.related_products` only on articles that discuss specific products
- Leave `custom.related_articles` blank for auto-populated related posts, or curate manually

