## Appendix C: Setup Script Reference

The automated setup script (`scripts/setup-store.mjs`) creates resources in 5 steps:

| Step | What It Creates | Count |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Metaobject definitions (benefit, faq_entry, blog_author, ingredient) | 4 |
| 2 | Product metafield definitions | 19 |
| 3 | Article metafield definitions | 12 |
| 4 | Pages (Ingredients, Quiz, Quiz Results, Contact) + optional (Store Locator, For Pharmacies) | 4–6 |
| 5 | Collections (Best Sellers, Scalp Serums, + range collections) | 2–6 |

Run with `--dry-run` first to preview changes. Run with `--step=N` to execute only one step.

After the script completes, you still need to:
1. Create a Blog and assign `blog.tara` / `article.tara` templates
2. Assign the `metaobject/ingredient` template in the Customizer
3. Add products to collections
4. Install apps (Klaviyo Reviews, Shopify Subscriptions, Tolstoy)
5. Replace all Spanish content with English copy (Step 19)
6. Upload image assets

